data.enText: a situation, an event, etc. that makes it difficult for you to do or achieve sth

data.chText: 学历不足可能成为谋职的主要障碍。
data.enText: A lack of qualifications can be a major obstacle to finding a job.

data.chText: 至此，我们已设法排除了设置在道路上的一切障碍。
data.enText: So far, we have managed to overcome all the obstacles that have been placed in our path.
an object that is in your way and that makes it difficult for you to move forward

data.chText: 此地遍布小溪、泥潭和其他天然障碍。
data.enText: The area was full of streams and bogs and other natural obstacles.
a fence, etc. for a horse to jump over

simple_means.memory_skill: ob 逆 + sta 站 + acle 物和抽象的概念 → 反着站的东西 → 障碍

ex.chText: 恐怖主义是和平的障碍。
ex.enText: Terrorism is an obstacle to peace.

ex.chText: 昨天他的车在比赛中撞上了障碍物。
ex.enText: His car hit an obstacle yesterday in the competition.

synonyms.bx: 指在达到目的或前行的过程中必须消除或绕过的障碍（物），可以是具体的或抽象的东西。

ex.chText: 他们已经决定要设置障碍以阻止竞争。
ex.enText: They have decided to set a bar to competition.

ex.chText: 那时在这一职业中，身为女性便是晋升的障碍。
ex.enText: At that time being a woman was a bar to promotion in this profession.

synonyms.bx: 指做某事的障碍，通常为抽象之物。

ex.chText: 贸易壁垒的消除对那个国家而言意义重大。
ex.enText: The removal of trade barriers means a lot to that country.

ex.chText: 女性取得事业成功的最大障碍是什么？
ex.enText: What remains the biggest barrier to women succeeding at work?

synonyms.bx: 多指产生阻碍或限制作用的政策、法律、问题等。

ex.chText: 排水管里可能有阻塞物。
ex.enText: There may be an obstruction in the drainpipe.

ex.chText: 把造成阻塞的车辆挪走。
ex.enText: Remove the vehicle that is causing the obstruction.

synonyms.bx: 指堵塞道路、通道、管道等的东西。

tr: an obstruction that stands in the way (and must be removed or surmounted or circumvented)
something immaterial that stands in the way and must be circumvented or surmounted
example: lack of imagination is an obstacle to one's advancement
the poverty of a district is an obstacle to good education
the filibuster was a major obstruction to the success of their plan

value.def: An obstacle is an object that makes it difficult for you to go where you want to go, because it is in your way.

example.ex: Most competition cars will only roll over if they hit an obstacle...
example.tran: 大多数赛车只有在撞上障碍物时才会翻车。

example.ex: He left her to navigate her own way round the trolleys and other obstacles.
example.tran: 他扔下她一个人在一堆手推车和其他障碍物之间绕来绕去。

value.def: You can refer to anything that makes it difficult for you to do something as an obstacle .

example.ex: Overcrowding remains a large obstacle to improving conditions...
example.tran: 过分拥挤仍然是改善环境的一大障碍。

example.ex: To succeed, you must learn to overcome obstacles.
example.tran: 必须学会克服困难才能成功。
